1
00:01:55,349 --> 00:01:57,885
Hi, everybody.
This is your cousin Brucie. Whoa!

2
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:01,989
Our summer romances are in full bloom,
and everybody's in love!

3
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:05,158
So cousins, here's a great song
from the Four Seasons.

4
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:15,269
That was the summer of 1963...

5
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:18,906
when everybody called me ""Baby""
and it didn't occur to me to mind.

6
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:29,950
That was before
President Kennedy was shot...

7
00:02:30,017 --> 00:02:31,985
before the Beatles came...

8
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:34,154
when I couldn't wait
to join the Peace Corps...

9
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:38,125
and I thought I'd never
find a guy as great as my dad.

10
00:02:47,634 --> 00:02:50,170
That was the summer
we went to Kellerman's.

11
00:03:09,389 --> 00:03:12,392
Ping-Pong in the west arcade,
softball in the east diamond.

12
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:14,728
All you Sandy Koufaxes,
get out there!

13
00:03:14,828 --> 00:03:17,264
Complimentary dance lessons
in the gazebo.

14
00:03:17,331 --> 00:03:19,967
Oh, my God.
Look at that!

15
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:24,171
Mom, I should've brought the coral
shoes. You said I was taking too much.

16
00:03:24,238 --> 00:03:26,874
Well, sweetheart,
you brought ten pairs.

17
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:29,443
But the coral shoes
matched that dress.

18
00:03:29,510 --> 00:03:31,178
This is not a tragedy.

19
00:03:31,245 --> 00:03:35,716
A tragedy is three men trapped in a mine
or police dogs used in Birmingham.

20
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:37,985
Monks burning themselves
in protest.

21
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:39,453
Butt out, Baby.

22
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:43,257
Okay, we got horseshoes
on the south lawn in 15 minutes!

23
00:03:43,357 --> 00:03:46,293
We've got splish-splash
the water class down by the lake.

24
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,997
We have the still life art class.
We got volleyball and croquet.

25
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:52,599
And for you older folks,
we got sacks!

26
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:55,369
Doc!

27
00:03:55,369 --> 00:03:56,703
Doc!

28
00:03:57,437 --> 00:03:58,639
Max!

29
00:03:58,739 --> 00:04:03,477
Doc, after all these years
I finally got you up on my mountain.

30
00:04:04,378 --> 00:04:05,812
How's the blood pressure?

31
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:07,814
I want you girls to know...

32
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:11,285
if it were not for this man,
I'd be standing here dead.

33
00:04:12,119 --> 00:04:14,555
- Billy, get the bags.
- Right away, Doc.

34
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:17,824
I kept the best cabin
for you and your beautiful girls.

35
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,730
Hey, thanks a lot.

36
00:04:23,797 --> 00:04:25,499
You want a job here?

37
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:28,735
There's a merengue class in
the gazebo in the next few minutes.

38
00:04:28,802 --> 00:04:31,505
The greatest teacher.
Used to be a Rockette.

39
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:35,576
It's his first real vacation
in six years, Max. Take it easy.

40
00:04:35,642 --> 00:04:38,512
Three weeks here,
it'll feel like a year.

41
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:42,149
One, two, three, four! Stomp
those grapes and stomp some more!

42
00:04:42,249 --> 00:04:46,386
One, two, three, four!
Listen to the music!

43
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:47,855
Sorry.

44
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:49,690
Move your caboose
and shake it loose!

45
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:53,594
One, two, three, four!
Start the train!

46
00:04:58,098 --> 00:05:00,868
Come on, men!
Follow me into a round robin!

47
00:05:01,935 --> 00:05:04,171
Ladies, the inner circle!

48
00:05:14,248 --> 00:05:15,816
Come on, ladies!

49
00:05:15,883 --> 00:05:20,320
God wouldn't have given you maracas
if he didn't want you to shake them!

50
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:27,427
Okay now, ladies,
when I say ""stop""...

51
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:30,497
you're gonna find
the man of your dreams.

52
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:32,833
Stop!

53
00:05:34,535 --> 00:05:38,639
Remember, he's the boss on
the dance floor, if nowhere else.

54
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:50,751
Mom, Dad, I'm going up
to the main house to look around.

55
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,091
There are two kinds of help here.

56
00:06:31,191 --> 00:06:33,360
You waiters are
all college guys...

57
00:06:33,427 --> 00:06:37,331
and I went to Harvard
and Yale to hire you.

58
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,367
And why did I do that? Why?

59
00:06:41,768 --> 00:06:44,571
I shouldn't have to remind you.
This is a family place.

60
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:48,442
That means you keep your fingers out
of the water, hair out of the soup...

61
00:06:48,542 --> 00:06:50,711
and show the goddamn
daughters a good time.

62
00:06:51,545 --> 00:06:52,946
All the daughters.

63
00:06:54,448 --> 00:06:56,617
Even the dogs.

64
00:06:56,717 --> 00:06:59,453
Schlepp 'em out to the terrace,
show 'em the stars.

65
00:06:59,553 --> 00:07:01,822
- Romance 'em any way you want.
- Got that, guys?

66
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,891
Hey, hold it!
Hold it.

67
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:09,429
Well, if it isn't
the entertainment staff.

68
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:11,798
Listen, wise ass,
you got your own rules.

69
00:07:11,899 --> 00:07:14,067
Dance with the daughters.
Teach 'em the mambo...

70
00:07:14,134 --> 00:07:16,770
the cha-cha,
anything they pay for.

71
00:07:16,837 --> 00:07:18,438
That's it.

72
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:20,707
That's where it ends.

73
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:24,444
No funny business, no conversations,
and keep you hands off!

74
00:07:27,347 --> 00:07:31,018
It's the same at all these places. Some
ass in the woods, but no conversation.

75
00:07:31,118 --> 00:07:33,020
Watch it, Rodriguez.

76
00:07:35,255 --> 00:07:39,159
Can you keep that straight, Johnny?
What you can't lay your hands on?

77
00:07:43,597 --> 00:07:47,367
Just put your pickle on everybody's
plate, and leave the hard stuff to me.

78
00:07:54,041 --> 00:07:56,610
Sit down and I'll
get you some wine.

79
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,012
Thank you, Max.

80
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:04,051
This is Dr. and Mrs. Houseman.

81
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:08,188
Baby, Lisa, this is your waiter,
Robbie Gould.

82
00:08:08,288 --> 00:08:10,958
Yale medical school.

83
00:08:11,024 --> 00:08:14,962
These people are my special guests.
Give them anything they want.

84
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:16,964
- Enjoy.
- Thanks, Max.

85
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:25,873
Look at all this leftover food. Are
there still starving children in Europe?

86
00:08:25,973 --> 00:08:28,675
- Try Southeast Asia, Ma.
- Right.

87
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:31,345
Robbie, Baby wants to send
her leftover pot roast...

88
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:34,548
to Southeast Asia,
so anything you don't finish, wrap up.

89
00:08:35,482 --> 00:08:38,085
Max, our Baby's gonna
change the world.

90
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:41,522
- And what are you gonna do, Missy?
- Lisa's gonna decorate it.

91
00:08:41,622 --> 00:08:43,690
She already does.

92
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:49,630
Doc, I want you to meet someone.
My grandson Neil.

93
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:52,099
Goes to the Cornell School
of Hotel Management.

94
00:08:52,199 --> 00:08:54,434
Baby's starting
Mount Holyoke in the fall.

95
00:08:55,435 --> 00:08:57,171
Oh, great.

96
00:09:05,846 --> 00:09:07,414
Are you going to major in English?

97
00:09:07,514 --> 00:09:10,951
No. Economics of
underdeveloped countries.

98
00:09:11,018 --> 00:09:14,421
- I'm going into the Peace Corps.
- After the final show...

99
00:09:14,521 --> 00:09:18,292
I'm going to Mississippi with
a couple of busboys, freedom ride.

100
00:09:37,711 --> 00:09:40,280
This is our own Tito Suarez.

101
00:10:27,528 --> 00:10:29,963
Mambo!
Yeah! Come on!

102
00:10:37,204 --> 00:10:39,339
Who's that?

103
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:41,842
Oh, them.
They're the dance people.

104
00:10:41,909 --> 00:10:44,912
They're here to keep
the guests happy.

105
00:11:07,568 --> 00:11:11,705
They shouldn't show off with each other.
That's not gonna sell lessons.

106
00:12:28,615 --> 00:12:31,185
- Hi, kids. Having fun?
- Yeah.

107
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:35,122
Actually, I've gotta excuse myself.
I'm in charge of the games tonight.

108
00:12:35,189 --> 00:12:37,925
Would you like to help me
get things started?

109
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:39,660
Sure she would.

110
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,104
This'll only hurt for a minute.
You've got Blue Cross, right?

111
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,983
Was that good for you?

112
00:13:03,016 --> 00:13:06,653
And for being such a good sport,
here you go!

113
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:15,128
I finally met a girl
exactly like my mother.

114
00:13:15,229 --> 00:13:18,298
Dresses like her, acts like her.
So I brought her home.

115
00:13:18,332 --> 00:13:20,300
My father doesn't like her!

116
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:23,871
Go figure.

117
00:14:12,853 --> 00:14:15,489
- Hi.
- How'd you get here?

118
00:14:15,522 --> 00:14:17,157
- I was taking a walk.
- Go back.

119
00:14:17,191 --> 00:14:19,193
Let me help you.
What's up there?

120
00:14:19,293 --> 00:14:21,195
No guests allowed.
House rules.

121
00:14:21,295 --> 00:14:25,732
Why don't you go back to the playhouse?
I saw you dancing with little boss man.

122
00:14:30,571 --> 00:14:32,539
Can you keep a secret?

123
00:14:34,842 --> 00:14:37,377
Your parents would kill you.

124
00:14:37,477 --> 00:14:39,379
Max would kill me.

125
00:15:32,466 --> 00:15:34,801
Where'd they learn to do that?

126
00:15:34,902 --> 00:15:36,737
Where?

127
00:15:36,803 --> 00:15:39,806
I don't know. Kids are doing it
in their basements back home.

128
00:15:41,108 --> 00:15:43,076
Wanna try it?

129
00:15:43,911 --> 00:15:45,846
Come on, Baby.

130
00:16:22,816 --> 00:16:25,953
Can you imagine dancing like this
on the main floor...

131
00:16:26,019 --> 00:16:28,455
home of the family fox-trot?

132
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:31,024
Max would close
the place down first.

133
00:17:03,156 --> 00:17:05,425
That's my cousin, Johnny Castle.

134
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:08,562
He got me the job here.

135
00:17:27,581 --> 00:17:30,083
- They look great together.
- Yeah.

136
00:17:30,117 --> 00:17:32,586
You'd think they were
a couple, wouldn't you?

137
00:17:32,653 --> 00:17:36,423
- Aren't they?
- No, not since we were kids.

138
00:18:16,129 --> 00:18:16,163
Do you love me?

139
00:18:16,163 --> 00:18:18,065
Do you love me?

140
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:40,654
Yo, cousin, what's she doing here?

141
00:18:41,321 --> 00:18:43,991
She came with me.
She's with me.

142
00:18:44,057 --> 00:18:45,893
I carried a watermelon.

143
00:18:51,899 --> 00:18:53,967
I carried a watermelon?

144
00:19:27,701 --> 00:19:29,870
Bend your knees. Down.

145
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,109
Watch. Watch my eyes.

146
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:38,679
Good.

147
00:19:42,816 --> 00:19:44,351
That's better.

148
00:19:49,223 --> 00:19:51,191
Good. Now roll this way.

149
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:54,695
Now watch.

150
00:20:04,705 --> 00:20:06,373
Look.

151
00:20:17,184 --> 00:20:18,919
Love man!

152
00:20:54,588 --> 00:20:58,058
Ladies, join our hair-raising
wig show.

153
00:20:58,125 --> 00:21:00,093
Try your Sandra Dee,
Jackie Kennedy...

154
00:21:00,194 --> 00:21:02,896
or Elizabeth Taylor-Cleopatra wig.

155
00:21:02,930 --> 00:21:06,433
- I'll knock with three.
- Look at that cute fella.

156
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,769
Look at these hands.
They're golden hands.

157
00:21:11,471 --> 00:21:14,441
My God, it's Cleopatra!
I feel like such an ""asp"".

158
00:21:14,508 --> 00:21:16,777
You look ten years younger.

159
00:21:16,844 --> 00:21:19,780
At 10:.15, by the pool,
we have calisthenics.

160
00:21:19,813 --> 00:21:23,116
Then on the west porch, we have
a symposium by Rabbi Maurice Sherman...

161
00:21:23,217 --> 00:21:26,119
on the psychology
of insult comedians.

162
00:21:27,855 --> 00:21:30,858
So I say, ""Ask not what your waiter
can do for you...

163
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:33,427
but what you can do
for your waiter.""

164
00:21:33,493 --> 00:21:36,463
If tips keep up, I'll have enough
for my Alfa Romeo.

165
00:21:37,865 --> 00:21:39,700
That's my favorite car.

166
00:21:41,869 --> 00:21:44,137
Ladies, you look very lovely.

167
00:21:45,239 --> 00:21:49,109
Baby, would you cover for me tonight?
Tell Mom and Dad I went to lie down.

168
00:21:49,142 --> 00:21:50,944
Where are you going?

169
00:21:51,011 --> 00:21:54,982
To the golf course. There's
a pretty view from the first tee.

170
00:21:58,185 --> 00:22:00,521
Good. Thanks.

171
00:22:07,628 --> 00:22:10,831
So you were really a Rockette?

172
00:22:10,898 --> 00:22:12,966
I think you're a wonderful dancer.

173
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:16,470
Yeah? Well, my mother kicked me out
when I was 16.

174
00:22:16,503 --> 00:22:20,174
I've been dancing ever since. It's the
only thing I ever wanted to do anyway.

175
00:22:21,542 --> 00:22:23,477
I envy you.

176
00:22:47,334 --> 00:22:51,371
- Aren't you dancing, Doc?
- We're waiting for a waltz.

177
00:22:52,906 --> 00:22:56,944
Hi, Max. Aren't my dance lessons
starting to pay off?

178
00:22:57,010 --> 00:23:00,514
You look great, Vivian!
Terrific!

179
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:07,688
That's Vivian Pressman,
one of the bungalow bunnies.

180
00:23:09,356 --> 00:23:12,326
That's what we call the women
who stay here all week.

181
00:23:13,126 --> 00:23:16,063
The husbands only come up
on weekends.

182
00:23:16,129 --> 00:23:19,499
Moe Pressman's a big card player.
He'll join our game.

183
00:23:21,101 --> 00:23:23,904
- Moe coming up on Friday?
- Friday.

184
00:23:24,872 --> 00:23:27,241
He's away a lot. I know.

185
00:23:28,542 --> 00:23:30,544
It's a hardship.

186
00:23:36,683 --> 00:23:40,254
Where's Penny?
Everybody's been asking for her.

187
00:23:41,722 --> 00:23:45,692
What do you mean, where's Penny?
She's taking a break.

188
00:23:45,726 --> 00:23:48,262
As long as it's not
an all-night break.

189
00:23:52,399 --> 00:23:54,935
Come on, doll. Let's take a walk.

190
00:24:04,344 --> 00:24:07,781
I love to watch your hair
blowing in the breeze.

191
00:24:11,351 --> 00:24:13,620
Maybe my parents
are looking for me.

192
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,455
Baby, don't worry.

193
00:24:15,556 --> 00:24:19,293
If they think you're with me, they'll be
the happiest parents at Kellerman's.

194
00:24:21,495 --> 00:24:23,430
I have to say it.

195
00:24:23,497 --> 00:24:26,500
- I'm known as the catch of the county.
- I'm sure you are.

196
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:29,670
Last week I took a girl away
from Jamie, the lifeguard.

197
00:24:29,770 --> 00:24:34,942
And he said to her,
""What does he have that I don't have?""

198
00:24:35,008 --> 00:24:38,312
And she said, ""Two hotels.""

199
00:24:40,347 --> 00:24:41,481
Robbie.

200
00:24:42,382 --> 00:24:44,384
I don't hear an apology.

201
00:24:44,484 --> 00:24:49,690
Go back to Mommy and Daddy and listen.
Maybe you'll hear one in your dreams.

202
00:24:51,859 --> 00:24:54,661
I'm sorry you had
to see that, Baby.

203
00:24:55,596 --> 00:24:58,031
Sometimes in this world...

204
00:24:58,131 --> 00:25:00,667
you see things
you don't wanna see.

205
00:25:05,239 --> 00:25:07,174
You hungry?

206
00:25:08,041 --> 00:25:09,676
Come on.

207
00:25:15,716 --> 00:25:19,686
So, Baby, what do you want?
You can have anything you want.

208
00:25:20,888 --> 00:25:23,490
A brownie, some milk...

209
00:25:23,557 --> 00:25:27,060
Ieftover rice pudding,
beets...

210
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,862
cabbage roll...

211
00:25:33,066 --> 00:25:35,402
fruit salad, sweet gherkins?

212
00:25:35,435 --> 00:25:39,540
Neil, look, I'm sorry.
I better go check on Lisa.

213
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,375
Yeah.

214
00:26:11,104 --> 00:26:14,107
- Why's she here?
- In case Neil comes back.

215
00:26:14,141 --> 00:26:16,243
Penny just doesn't think.

216
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:19,279
She wouldn't do anything
stupid, would she?

217
00:26:20,113 --> 00:26:23,851
So, what's wrong?
What's the matter with her?

218
00:26:24,885 --> 00:26:27,387
- She's knocked up, Baby.
- Billy!

219
00:26:29,089 --> 00:26:33,060
- What's he gonna do about it?
- ""What's he gonna do about it?""

220
00:26:33,794 --> 00:26:35,395
It's mine, right?

221
00:26:35,462 --> 00:26:38,131
- Right away you think it's mine.
- But I thought...

222
00:26:55,782 --> 00:26:58,452
It's okay. Johnny's here.

223
00:27:02,956 --> 00:27:05,459
I'm never gonna let anything
happen to you.

224
00:27:09,696 --> 00:27:11,632
We got to go.

225
00:27:13,767 --> 00:27:16,136
Just hold on. Just hold on.

226
00:27:16,170 --> 00:27:18,772
Good girl. Good girl.

227
00:27:23,377 --> 00:27:26,380
What do you think you're doing?
You're in trouble, you talk to me.

228
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:28,916
I'll take care of it.

229
00:27:28,982 --> 00:27:32,486
You should've come to me
in the first place.

230
00:27:32,553 --> 00:27:35,956
Forget it, Johnny. I'm not taking
what's left of your salary.

231
00:27:35,989 --> 00:27:39,960
- Penny, that's my business.
- Besides, it wouldn't be enough.

232
00:27:49,803 --> 00:27:52,206
Oh, God, it's hopeless!

233
00:27:52,306 --> 00:27:54,474
Don't say that.

234
00:27:54,508 --> 00:27:57,511
There's gotta be a way
to work it out.

235
00:28:00,113 --> 00:28:03,483
Baby? Is that your name?

236
00:28:04,384 --> 00:28:06,153
You know what, Baby?

237
00:28:07,187 --> 00:28:09,656
You don't know shit
about my problems.

238
00:28:10,858 --> 00:28:12,826
I told her.

239
00:28:12,893 --> 00:28:18,365
Jesus! She's gonna tell her management
boyfriend and then we'll all get fired.

240
00:28:18,432 --> 00:28:22,736
Why not skywrite it? ""Penny got
knocked up by Robbie, the creep.""

241
00:28:22,836 --> 00:28:25,439
- Look--
- No, Baby.

242
00:28:26,673 --> 00:28:29,510
One of the counselors
knows a doctor, a real M.D....

