end-of-the-season talent show...

488
00:59:38,645 --> 00:59:40,647
beginning in the playhouse.

489
00:59:47,487 --> 00:59:50,324
- Everyone gonna be in the show?
- We're leaving tomorrow.

490
00:59:50,357 --> 00:59:52,526
Miss the weekend traffic.

491
00:59:52,626 --> 00:59:54,494
But we're paid up 'til Sunday.

492
00:59:54,528 --> 00:59:57,531
- And miss the show?
- I said we're leaving tomorrow.

493
00:59:57,631 --> 01:00:00,634
- I was going to sing in the show.
- It's the big event.

494
01:00:00,667 --> 01:00:03,036
People bring their own arrangements.
You don't want to miss it.

495
01:00:03,136 --> 01:00:05,138
Baby, I need you for props.

496
01:00:06,673 --> 01:00:09,843
Why would you want to leave early?

497
01:00:16,817 --> 01:00:19,653
It was just an idea.
We can stay if you want to.

498
01:00:23,357 --> 01:00:26,960
- So, what were you planning to sing?
- ""l Feel Pretty.""

499
01:00:27,027 --> 01:00:30,030
Or ""What Do the Simple Folk Do?""

500
01:00:30,063 --> 01:00:33,867
Or ""l Feel Pretty.""
What do you think, Daddy?

501
01:00:45,879 --> 01:00:47,314
You look much better.

502
01:00:50,017 --> 01:00:53,554
You just missed your father.
He's such a wonderful man.

503
01:00:55,422 --> 01:00:57,991
I'm sorry. I didn't realize--

504
01:00:58,058 --> 01:01:00,394
You couldn't have. It's okay.

505
01:01:12,406 --> 01:01:15,209
- So, how you doin'?
- I'm okay.

506
01:01:16,777 --> 01:01:19,246
Dr. Houseman says
I'm going to be fine.

507
01:01:20,581 --> 01:01:24,384
- I can still have children.
- Oh, Penny, that's really great.

508
01:01:26,954 --> 01:01:29,723
So, how did it go last night?

509
01:01:29,790 --> 01:01:31,758
Good.

510
01:01:33,060 --> 01:01:37,564
Fine. I didn't do the lifts,
but it was good.

511
01:01:48,275 --> 01:01:52,980
Well, I guess I gonna go.

512
01:01:55,148 --> 01:01:56,783
See ya.

513
01:02:04,858 --> 01:02:07,160
- So, he says you're going to be fine?
- What are you doing?

514
01:02:07,261 --> 01:02:10,697
- I'll tell Max your grandmother died.
- How many times have you told me...

515
01:02:10,797 --> 01:02:13,534
never get mixed-up with them?

516
01:02:13,634 --> 01:02:15,536
I know what I'm doing.

517
01:02:16,637 --> 01:02:20,407
You listen to me.
You've got to stop it now.

518
01:02:36,356 --> 01:02:39,560
Look, I gotta run.
I got a lesson with the Kramers.

519
01:02:39,660 --> 01:02:42,029
They'll kill each other
if I'm not there.

520
01:02:42,095 --> 01:02:44,531
Well, sure. You've gotta go.

521
01:02:47,334 --> 01:02:48,735
I'll see ya.

522
01:03:08,288 --> 01:03:11,191
It's rainy day game time.
Pin the tail on the guest.

523
01:03:11,291 --> 01:03:13,694
Win ten boxes of Kleenex
or a billy goat!

524
01:03:14,761 --> 01:03:18,232
God, I am so sick of this rain.

525
01:03:18,332 --> 01:03:21,034
Remind me not to take my honeymoon
at Niagara Falls.

526
01:03:21,101 --> 01:03:24,238
So, you go to Acapulco.
It'll be fine.

527
01:03:24,304 --> 01:03:27,941
Where is my beige
iridescent lipstick?

528
01:03:28,041 --> 01:03:30,210
I know I put it in this drawer.

529
01:03:30,310 --> 01:03:32,513
Baby, where are you going
in this weather?

530
01:03:32,579 --> 01:03:35,182
Uh, they're having charades
in the west lobby.

531
01:03:35,249 --> 01:03:38,185
Quite the little joiner,
aren't we?

532
01:03:52,966 --> 01:03:56,336
- Have you had many women?
- What?

533
01:03:59,106 --> 01:04:00,941
Baby, come on.

534
01:04:00,974 --> 01:04:02,943
Tell me. I want to know.

535
01:04:14,788 --> 01:04:16,924
You gotta understand
what it's like.

536
01:04:16,990 --> 01:04:19,426
You come from the streets
and suddenly you're up here.

537
01:04:19,526 --> 01:04:23,397
Women are throwing themselves
at you and they smell so good.

538
01:04:23,463 --> 01:04:25,566
They really take care
of themselves.

539
01:04:25,632 --> 01:04:28,068
I never knew women
could be like that.

540
01:04:28,135 --> 01:04:31,405
They're so goddamn rich you think
they must know about everything.

541
01:04:31,471 --> 01:04:34,174
They're slippin' their room keys
in my hand two and three times a day--

542
01:04:34,241 --> 01:04:38,445
different women--
so, I think I'm scorin' big, right?

543
01:04:38,545 --> 01:04:42,950
You think, ""They wouldn't be doing this
if they didn't care about me, right?""

544
01:04:44,151 --> 01:04:47,120
That's all right. I understand.
You were just using them, that's all.

545
01:04:49,089 --> 01:04:50,557
No, that's not it.

546
01:04:51,458 --> 01:04:53,760
That's the thing.
It wasn't like that.

547
01:04:55,863 --> 01:04:57,965
They were using me.

548
01:05:25,526 --> 01:05:27,461
What's your real name, Baby?

549
01:05:29,463 --> 01:05:33,634
Frances, for the first woman
in the Cabinet.

550
01:05:35,836 --> 01:05:39,206
Frances.
That's a real grownup name.

551
01:05:52,386 --> 01:05:54,821
I've decided to go
all the way with Robbie.

552
01:05:57,391 --> 01:06:01,094
No, not with someone like him.

553
01:06:01,161 --> 01:06:05,532
Do you think if we came back for a
ten-year anniversary, it would be free?

554
01:06:05,632 --> 01:06:09,102
It's just wrong this way.
It should be with someone--

555
01:06:09,203 --> 01:06:13,807
With someone that
you sort of love.

556
01:06:13,841 --> 01:06:18,078
Come on.
You don't care about me.

557
01:06:18,178 --> 01:06:21,181
You wouldn't care if I humped
the entire army...

558
01:06:21,248 --> 01:06:24,418
as long as we were on the right side
of the Ho Chi Minh Trail.

559
01:06:24,518 --> 01:06:29,356
What you care about is that
you're not Daddy's girl anymore.

560
01:06:29,389 --> 01:06:31,859
He listens when I talk now.

561
01:06:32,993 --> 01:06:34,394
You hate that.

562
01:06:51,578 --> 01:06:54,314
Two, three, cha-cha-cha.

563
01:06:54,414 --> 01:06:57,284
My frame.
Where's my pleasing arc?

564
01:06:57,384 --> 01:07:00,921
Spaghetti arms! Would you
give me some tension, please?

565
01:07:02,789 --> 01:07:06,159
You're invading my dance space.
This is my dance space.

566
01:07:06,226 --> 01:07:08,629
That's yours. Let's cha-cha.

567
01:07:14,801 --> 01:07:17,471
Don't look down.
Look right here.

568
01:07:26,413 --> 01:07:31,151
- How you call your lover boy?
- Come here, lover boy.

569
01:07:31,251 --> 01:07:34,788
- And if he doesn't answer?
- Oh, lover boy.

570
01:07:34,888 --> 01:07:38,258
- And if still doesn't answer?
- I simply say...

571
01:07:38,292 --> 01:07:41,061
Baby

572
01:07:41,128 --> 01:07:43,964
O-Oh, baby

573
01:07:45,065 --> 01:07:47,901
My sweet baby

574
01:07:48,936 --> 01:07:50,904
You're the one

575
01:08:06,286 --> 01:08:07,788
Takin' dance lessons?

576
01:08:08,822 --> 01:08:10,791
I could teach ya, kid.

577
01:08:15,495 --> 01:08:18,465
My grandfather put me in charge
of the final show.

578
01:08:18,532 --> 01:08:20,834
I want to talk to you
about the last dance.

579
01:08:20,934 --> 01:08:24,004
I'd like to shake things up a bit.

580
01:08:24,104 --> 01:08:26,707
You know, move with the times.

581
01:08:26,807 --> 01:08:28,809
I've got a lot of ideas.

582
01:08:28,876 --> 01:08:30,978
I've been working
with the staff kids...

583
01:08:31,011 --> 01:08:34,548
on a cross between a Cuban rhythm
and soul dancing.

584
01:08:34,648 --> 01:08:37,417
Whoa, boy.

585
01:08:37,518 --> 01:08:39,753
Way over your head here.

586
01:08:39,853 --> 01:08:43,824
You always do the mambo, huh?

587
01:08:43,891 --> 01:08:47,127
Why not dance this year's
final dance...

588
01:08:49,162 --> 01:08:51,031
to the pachenga?

589
01:08:52,199 --> 01:08:53,333
Right.

590
01:08:55,536 --> 01:08:59,239
Well, you're free to do the same,
tired number as last year if you want...

591
01:08:59,339 --> 01:09:02,242
but next year we'll find
another dance person...

592
01:09:02,342 --> 01:09:04,711
- who'll only be too happy--
- Sure, Neil. No problem.

593
01:09:06,914 --> 01:09:09,082
We'll end the season
with the pachenga.

594
01:09:09,183 --> 01:09:10,617
Great idea.

595
01:09:17,191 --> 01:09:21,562
Sometimes he's hard to talk to,
but the ladies seem to like him.

596
01:09:21,595 --> 01:09:24,598
See that he gives you the full half-hour
you're paying him for, kid.

597
01:09:33,473 --> 01:09:36,543
That little wimp. He wouldn't know a
new idea if it hit him in the pachenga.

598
01:09:36,610 --> 01:09:38,912
I could have told him
some new ideas.

599
01:09:39,012 --> 01:09:41,014
Why did you let him
talk to you that way?

600
01:09:41,081 --> 01:09:43,550
- What, fight the boss man?
- You tell him your ideas.

601
01:09:43,617 --> 01:09:46,420
- He's a person like everyone else.
- Look, I know these people.

602
01:09:46,486 --> 01:09:49,189
They are rich and they're mean.
They won't listen to me.

603
01:09:49,256 --> 01:09:51,658
Why not fight harder?
Make them listen.

604
01:09:51,758 --> 01:09:54,628
Because I need this goddamned job
lined up for next summer.

605
01:09:55,729 --> 01:09:57,798
My dad calls me today.

606
01:09:57,898 --> 01:10:00,501
""Good news,"" he says. ""Uncle Paul
can finally get you in the union.""

607
01:10:00,601 --> 01:10:01,835
What union?

608
01:10:03,036 --> 01:10:06,940
The House Painters and Plasterers
Local Number 179 at your service.

609
01:10:15,082 --> 01:10:17,618
I've been thinking a lot
about the Domino Theory.

610
01:10:17,684 --> 01:10:20,053
Now, when Viet Nam falls,
is China Next?

611
01:10:22,856 --> 01:10:24,791
I don't think they saw us.

612
01:10:35,969 --> 01:10:37,437
Fight harder, huh?

613
01:10:38,472 --> 01:10:42,242
I don't see you fightin' so hard,
tellin' Daddy I'm your guy.

614
01:10:42,309 --> 01:10:44,478
I will. With my father,
it's complicated.

615
01:10:44,545 --> 01:10:46,980
- I will tell him.
- I don't believe you, Baby.

616
01:10:50,651 --> 01:10:52,119
I don't think...

617
01:10:53,654 --> 01:10:56,423
that you ever had
any intention of telling him.

618
01:10:57,491 --> 01:10:58,625
Ever.

619
01:11:09,670 --> 01:11:09,670
Well, Cousin, it's almost over.
Labor Day weekend is here.

620
01:11:09,670 --> 01:11:12,506
Well, Cousin, it's almost over.
Labor Day weekend is here.

621
01:11:12,539 --> 01:11:16,276
Soon it's back to the old books and
back to work. What a terrible thought!

622
01:11:26,019 --> 01:11:27,988
Have you seen Johnny?

623
01:11:43,770 --> 01:11:45,072
I'm sorry.

624
01:11:49,543 --> 01:11:51,478
Looks like I picked
the wrong sister.

625
01:11:51,545 --> 01:11:54,348
That's okay, Baby.
I went slummin' too.

626
01:12:12,199 --> 01:12:13,867
Hit me.

627
01:12:20,941 --> 01:12:22,910
Get out of here.
You're not worth it.

628
01:13:21,101 --> 01:13:23,303
Win big, Moe.

629
01:13:23,403 --> 01:13:24,638
As always.

630
01:13:42,189 --> 01:13:46,026
This is our last night together, lover.
I've got something worked out for us.

631
01:14:08,682 --> 01:14:10,984
Excuse me, sir.
The pirate number's next.

632
01:14:11,051 --> 01:14:13,353
Oh, thanks.
Hey, kid.

633
01:14:13,420 --> 01:14:16,156
I've been playing cards all weekend
and I've got an all-night game tonight.

634
01:14:16,223 --> 01:14:19,726
Why don't you give my wife
some extra dance lessons?

635
01:14:28,802 --> 01:14:30,704
I'm sorry, Mr. Pressman...

636
01:14:30,804 --> 01:14:33,273
but I'm booked up for
the whole weekend with the show.

637
01:14:33,373 --> 01:14:35,576
I won't have time
for anything else.

638
01:14:35,642 --> 01:14:38,846
I don't think it'd be fair
to take the money.

639
01:15:03,604 --> 01:15:06,440
I've decided tonight's the night
with Robbie.

640
01:15:06,473 --> 01:15:08,675
He doesn't even know yet.

641
01:15:44,411 --> 01:15:45,646
It's me.

642
01:15:50,817 --> 01:15:52,152
Holy shit!

643
01:16:13,207 --> 01:16:15,309
You wanna hear somethin' crazy?

644
01:16:19,646 --> 01:16:21,114
Last night l--

645
01:16:22,282 --> 01:16:26,553
I dreamt we were walking along
and we met your father.

646
01:16:26,620 --> 01:16:29,289
He said, ""Come on,""
and he put his arm around me.

647
01:16:30,991 --> 01:16:33,093
Just like he did with Robbie.

648
01:17:20,374 --> 01:17:25,612
You know how you feel when you see a
patient and you think he's all right...

649
01:17:25,712 --> 01:17:28,682
then you look at the X rays
and it's nothing like you thought?

650
01:17:28,715 --> 01:17:29,983
What happened?

651
01:17:30,050 --> 01:17:33,520
It's exactly what it's like when you
find out one of your staff's a thief.

652
01:17:33,554 --> 01:17:37,224
Moe Pressman's wallet was stolen
when he was playing pinochle last night.

653
01:17:37,324 --> 01:17:40,327
It was in his jacket hanging
on the back of his chair.

654
01:17:40,394 --> 01:17:44,631
He had it at 1:30 and when he
checked again at quarter of 4::00...

655
01:17:44,698 --> 01:17:47,100
it was missing.

656
01:17:47,201 --> 01:17:51,705
Vivian thinks she remembers
this dance kid Johnny...

657
01:17:51,772 --> 01:17:53,040
walking by.

658
01:17:54,107 --> 01:17:58,011
So we ask him,
""You have an alibi for last night?""

659
01:17:58,045 --> 01:18:00,280
He says he was alone
in his room reading.

660
01:18:01,648 --> 01:18:04,084
There are no books
in Johnny's room!

661
01:18:06,053 --> 01:18:08,121
There's been a mistake.
I know Johnny didn't do it.

662
01:18:08,222 --> 01:18:10,657
There's been similar thefts at the
Sheldrake. It's happened here before.

663
01:18:10,724 --> 01:18:13,093
- Three other wallets.
- I know he didn't do it.

664
01:18:13,193 --> 01:18:15,262
Stay out of it, Baby.

665
01:18:15,362 --> 01:18:19,199
Wait. Don't put those
tables together. Come on.

666
01:18:21,435 --> 01:18:25,506
Daddy, I need your help.
I know Johnny didn't take Moe's wallet.

667
01:18:25,572 --> 01:18:27,941
- Oh? How do you know?
- I can't tell you.

668
01:18:28,041 --> 01:18:32,813
- Just please trust me, Daddy.
- I'm sorry, Baby. I can't.

669
01:18:32,913 --> 01:18:34,982
This Danish is pure protein.

670
01:18:37,818 --> 01:18:41,522
Maybe Johnny didn't do it.
Anyone could've taken it.

671
01:18:41,588 --> 01:18:43,524
Maybe it was, uh--

672
01:18:43,590 --> 01:18:46,460
It could've been that little,
old couple, the Schumachers.

673
01:18:46,527 --> 01:18:49,763
- I saw her with a couple of wallets.
- Sylvia and Sidney?

674
01:18:49,830 --> 01:18:52,866
Baby, you don't go around
accusing innocent people.

675
01:18:52,966 --> 01:18:57,437
I even saw them at the Sheldrake. You
said something was stolen from there.

676
01:18:57,504 --> 01:19:01,108
I got an eyewitness
and the kid has no alibi.

677
01:19:01,175 --> 01:19:05,112
Come on, Neil. You'll learn
what it's like to fire an employee.

678
01:19:06,313 --> 01:19:09,816
Wait a minute. I know Johnny
didn't take the wallet.

679
01:19:09,883 --> 01:19:13,120
I know because he was
in his room all night.

680
01:19:13,187 --> 01:19:17,691
And the reason I know
is because I was with him.

681
01:19:42,115 --> 01:19:44,017
I told you I was
telling the truth.

682
01:19:48,889 --> 01:19:50,858
I'm sorry I lied to you.

683
01:19:53,727 --> 01:19:55,696
But you lied too.

684
01:19:57,898 --> 01:20:01,468
You told me everyone was alike
and deserved a fair break.

685
01:20:01,535 --> 01:20:03,637
But you meant everyone
who is like you.

686
01:20:06,373 --> 01:20:09,643
You told me you wanted me to change
the world, to make it better.

687
01:20:10,711 --> 01:20:13,347
But you meant by becoming
a lawyer or an economist...

688
01:20:13,380 --> 01:20:15,549
and marrying someone
from Harvard.

689
01:20:18,218 --> 01:20:20,754
I'm not proud of myself.

690
01:20:20,854 --> 01:20:24,358
But I'm in this family too. You can't
keep giving me the silent treatment.

691
01:20:27,895 --> 01:20:30,731
There are a lot of things about me
that aren't what you thought.

692
01:20:31,765 --> 01:20:34,735
But if you love me, you have to love
all the things about me.

693
01:20:37,404 --> 01:20:39,339
And I love you.

694
01:20:39,406 --> 01:20:43,977
I'm sorry I let you down.
I'm so sorry, Daddy.

695
01:20:44,878 --> 01:20:47,114
But you let me down too.

696
01:21:17,411 --> 01:21:19,613
I have been lookin'
for you all over.

697
01:21:20,614 --> 01:21:22,449
They found the Schumachers.

698
01:21:22,549 --> 01:21:24,852
Fingerprinted their water glasses.

699
01:21:24,952 --> 01:21:27,788
Found out they were wanted
in Arizona and in Florida...

700
01:21:27,855 --> 01:21:30,290
and they made a fortune
here this summer.

701
01:21:30,324 --> 01:21:32,292
So then it's all right.

702
01:21:33,427 --> 01:21:35,429
I knew it would work out.

703
01:21:35,495 --> 01:21:37,798
- I knew they'd have to apologize.
- I'm out, Baby.

704
01:21:43,036 --> 01:21:44,972
They fired you anyway
because of me.

705
01:21:46,640 --> 01:21:49,977
And if I leave quietly,
I'll get my summer bonus.

706
01:21:52,980 --> 01:21:54,882
So I did it for nothing.

707
01:21:54,982 --> 01:21:58,986
I hurt my family, you lost your job
anyway-- I did it for nothing!

708
01:21:59,052 --> 01:22:00,988
No, not for nothing.

709
01:22:01,054 --> 01:22:04,424
Nobody has ever done anything
like that for me before.

710
01:22:05,192 --> 01:22:08,428
You were right. You can't win
no matter what you do.

711
01:22:08,495 --> 01:22:11,965
Listen to me. I don't want
to hear that from you. You can.

712
01:22:13,867 --> 01:22:15,969
I used to think so.

713
01:22:37,558 --> 01:22:39,660
Dr. Houseman, can l, uh--

714
01:22:41,161 --> 01:22:44,198
Look, I'm going anyway and I know
what you must be thinking.

715
01:22:44,264 --> 01:22:47,234
You don't know
anything at all about me.

716
01:22:47,334 --> 01:22:50,037
I know you want Baby
to be like you.

717
01:22:50,070 --> 01:22:52,906
The kind of person
people look up to.

718
01:22:53,006 --> 01:22:55,209
Baby is like that.
If you could just see--

719
01:22:55,242 --> 01:22:58,212
Don't you tell me what to see.

720
01:22:58,245 --> 01:23:00,881
I see someone in front of me
who got his partner in trouble...

721
01:23:00,914 --> 01:23:03,350
and sent her off
to some butcher...

722
01:23:03,417 --> 01:23:06,687
while he moved on to an innocent,
young girl like my daughter.

723
01:23:11,859 --> 01:23:14,461
Yeah, I guess that's
what you would see.

724
01:23:30,010 --> 01:23:33,280
I can't imagine being here
without you even one day.

725
01:23:33,313 --> 01:23:37,084
Just think, you have more time
for horseshoes and croquet.

726
01:23:40,020 --> 01:23:42,756
Maybe they'll saw you
in seven pieces now.

727
01:23:45,158 --> 01:23:47,261
I guess we surprised everybody.

728
01:23:49,630 --> 01:23:51,565
I guess we did.

729
01:23:59,573 --> 01:24:01,475
Hardly would be sorry.

730
01:24:03,510 --> 01:24:04,978
Neither will l.

731
01:24:12,352 --> 01:24:13,787
I'll see ya.

732
01:25:09,977 --> 01:25:11,945
I'll do your hair.

733
01:25:14,047 --> 01:25:16,149
It could look pretty if--

734
01:25:22,055 --> 01:25:24,491
You're prettier your way.

735
01:25:24,558 --> 01:25:25,826
This way.

736
01:25:48,515 --> 01:25:52,786
Kellermans, we come together

737
01:25:52,886 --> 01:25:56,890
Singing all as one

738
01:25:56,990 --> 01:26:01,094
We have shared another season's

739
01:26:01,161 --> 01:26:05,098
Talent, play and fun

740
01:26:05,165 --> 01:26:09,269
Summer days will soon be over

741
01:26:09,369 --> 01:26:13,473
Soon the autumn starts

742
01:26:13,574 --> 01:26:17,477
And tonight the memories whisper

743
01:26:17,578 --> 01:26:20,948
Softly in our hearts

744
01:26:22,015 --> 01:26:25,886
Join hands and hearts and voices

745
01:26:25,953 --> 01:26:29,356
Voices, hearts and hands

746
01:26:29,423 --> 01:26:33,360
At Kellerman's
the friendships last

747
01:26:33,427 --> 01:26:37,965
Long as the mountain stands

748
01:26:38,031 --> 01:26:42,302
Daytime, nighttime, any hour

749
01:26:42,369 --> 01:26:46,240
Weather rain or shine

750
01:26:46,306 --> 01:26:50,511
Games and lectures
Jokes and music

751
01:26:50,577 --> 01:26:54,648
Happily combine

752
01:27:08,061 --> 01:27:09,963
Good luck in medical school, son.

753
01:27:12,165 --> 01:27:14,701
And I wanted to thank you for your
help with the Penny situation.

754
01:27:14,768 --> 01:27:18,605
- I guess we've all gotten into messes.
- What?

755
01:27:20,307 --> 01:27:23,110
I thought Baby told you.
Look, I'm not sure.

756
01:27:23,177 --> 01:27:26,413
Penny said so, but you know with girls
like that. They're liable to pin it...

757
01:27:26,446 --> 01:27:28,415
on any guy around.

758
01:27:34,655 --> 01:27:37,257
- What's the hot tip for the day?
- Finished.

759
01:27:38,325 --> 01:27:41,195
You and me, Tito.
We've seen it all, eh?

760
01:27:41,295 --> 01:27:46,366
Bubbah and Zeda serving the first
pasteurized milk to the boarders.

761
01:27:46,466 --> 01:27:48,635
Through the war years
when we didn't have any meat.

762
01:27:48,702 --> 01:27:51,438
Through the Depression
when we didn't have anything.

763
01:27:51,471 --> 01:27:53,974
Lots of changes, though, Max.

764
01:27:54,007 --> 01:27:57,511
It's not the changes
so much this time.

765
01:27:57,578 --> 01:28:00,147
It's that it all seems
to be ending.

766
01:28:00,214 --> 01:28:04,218
You think kids want to come with their
parents and take fox-trot lessons?

767
01:28:04,318 --> 01:28:07,454
Trips to Europe,
that's what the kids want.

768
01:28:08,522 --> 01:28:11,091
Twenty-two countries
in three days.

769
01:28:12,192 --> 01:28:14,461
It feels like
it's all slipping away.

770
01:28:15,662 --> 01:28:19,533
But the heartbeats of vacation

771
01:28:19,633 --> 01:28:23,504
There no cares are seen

772
01:28:23,570 --> 01:28:27,541
So let's join in
just one last chorus

773
01:28:27,641 --> 01:28:31,011
Visitors, staff and guests

774
01:28:31,044 --> 01:28:35,582
What we've shared
won't be forgotten

775
01:28:35,682 --> 01:28:38,719
Old friends are the best

776
01:29:14,254 --> 01:29:15,989
Nobody puts Baby in the corner.

777
01:29:17,758 --> 01:29:19,159
Come on.

778
01:29:39,913 --> 01:29:42,115
Sorry about
the disruption, folks...

779
01:29:42,182 --> 01:29:45,452
but I always do
the last dance of the season.

780
01:29:45,552 --> 01:29:48,555
This year somebody told me not to.

781
01:29:48,589 --> 01:29:52,426
So I'm gonna do my kind of dancin'
with a great partner...

782
01:29:53,260 --> 01:29:56,163
who's not only
a terrific dancer...

783
01:29:56,263 --> 01:29:58,732
but somebody who's taught me
that there are people...

784
01:29:58,765 --> 01:30:01,802
willing to stand up for other people
no matter what it costs them.

785
01:30:03,170 --> 01:30:05,739
Somebody who's taught me...

786
01:30:07,674 --> 01:30:09,776
about the kind of person
I want to be.

787
01:30:10,978 --> 01:30:12,446
Miss Frances Houseman.

788
01:30:13,280 --> 01:30:14,681
Sit down, Jake.

789
01:31:38,532 --> 01:31:40,601
I think she gets this from me.

790
01:34:35,209 --> 01:34:38,011
Do you have sheet music
on this stuff?

791
01:34:46,086 --> 01:34:49,189
I know you weren't the one
who got Penny in trouble.

792
01:34:51,358 --> 01:34:53,827
When I'm wrong, I say I'm wrong.

793
01:35:00,367 --> 01:35:02,302
You looked wonderful out there.

794
01:35:59,993 --> 01:36:02,095
Now l

795
01:36:02,162 --> 01:36:06,133
Had the time of my life

796
01:36:06,200 --> 01:36:10,370
No, I never felt
this way before

797
01:36:10,437 --> 01:36:12,840
Yes, I swear

798
01:36:12,906 --> 01:36:17,444
It's so true
And I owe it all to you

